description:
California Gov. Gavin Newsom issued a statewide order for nearly all of the state’s 40 million residents to “stay at home” amid the coronavirus pandemic. “We need to bend the curve in the state of California,” Newsom said in an announcement. “There’s a social contract here. People I think recognize the need to do more. They will adjust and adapt as they have.” The order took effect midnight on Friday. It bans gatherings outside and forces nonessential businesses to close in an effort to slow the spread of the virus.
Newsom added, “This is a moment we need to make tough decisions. This is a moment where we need some straight talk and we need to tell people the truth.” Public events have been canceled and bars, dine-in restaurants, gyms and clubs will be closed. Essential services such as grocery stores, pharmacies and banks will stay open.
Newsom’s office projected the virus will infect more than half of Californias within two months, according to a letter he sent to President Trump on Wednesday where he said the state has been disproportionality impacted. “In some parts of our state, our case rate is doubling every four days,” he wrote Trump.
